OL,3,CUK set to shed 163,000 jobs amid Iran
OL,4,Cwar fallout ` report
OL,6,FBritain is expected to lose 163,000
OL,7,Fjobs this year amid the economic woes
OL,8,Fcaused by the Iran war with lower
OL,9,Fincome regions set to be hit hardest,
OL,10,Faccording to a report.
OL,12,FThe Item Club's latest regional
OL,13,Foutlook warns that two of the UK's
OL,14,Flowest income regions ` South Wales
OL,15,Fand the Humber ` will suffer the most
OL,16,Fpainful jobs market woes in the next
OL,17,Fyear or so because of sharp energy
OL,18,Fprice rises.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778461395
OL,3,CUK set to shed 163,000 jobs amid Iran
OL,4,Cwar fallout ` report
OL,6,FThey are heavily reliant on
OL,7,Fmanufacturing and construction
OL,8,Findustries, which Item Club cautions
OL,9,Fwill shed jobs in response to higher
OL,10,Fcosts and supply disruption from the
OL,11,FMiddle East conflict.
OL,13,FThe report is predicting jobs to drop
OL,14,Fby 5,700 in South Wales and by 2,800
OL,15,Fin the Humber over 2026.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778461395
OL,3,CUK set to shed 163,000 jobs amid Iran
OL,4,Cwar fallout ` report
OL,6,FTim Lyne, economic adviser to the Item
OL,7,FClub, said: "Some of the lowest income
OL,8,Fregions will feel the biggest effects
OL,9,Fof the manufacturing and construction
OL,10,Fsectors reducing headcount in the face
OL,11,Fof rising energy prices and supply
OL,12,Fchain disruption.
OL,14,F"While consumers in these areas
OL,15,Ftypically have less rainy-day savings,
OL,16,Fwhich will reduce spending in the
OL,17,Fretail and hospitality sectors."
OL,26,@oD@MOUvD@AOUyD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
